column7: Genomic resource collection (GRC) for ornithology at Cincinnati Museum Center's Museum of Natural History and Science. Collection consists primarily of vouchered frozen tissues kept at -80 degrees Celsius as well as blood samples from banded birds, isolated genomic DNA and other materials for use in molecular genetic and other biomolecular studies.
